main event: A UFO was observed near Lancaster, Pennsylvania on 13 February 1957 by a civilian for five minutes.
interesting points: The observation lasted for five minutes, providing a substantial amount of time for the witness to examine the object.
The object was reported as stationary, indicating unusual behavior for a conventional aircraft or astronomical object.
The report suggests that the object was possibly a balloon, airplane, or astronomical in nature, leaving the conclusion inconclusive.
The sighting occurred in 1957, during a period of heightened UFO interest and numerous reported sightings.
The report is categorized under Project 10073, an official government program dedicated to investigating and documenting UFO sightings.
